heavens.	1
There	1
are	1
only	1
a	1
few	1
hundred	1
stars	1
within	1
five	1
hundred	1
trillion	1
miles	1
of	1
the	1
earth,	1
and	1
at	1
that	1
distance	1
the	1
"shift"	1
of	1
a	1
star	1
against	1
the	1
background	1
(parallax,	1
the	1
astronomer	1
calls	1
it)	1
is	1
so	1
minute	1
that	1
figures	1
are	1
very	1
uncertain.	1
At	1
this	1
point	1
the	1
astronomer	1
takes	1
up	1
a	1
new	1
method.	1
He	1
learns	1
the	1
different	1
types	1
of	1
stars,	1
and	1
then	1
