the	1
star	1
appeared	1
in	1
1901,	1
but	1
you	1
begin	1
to	1
realise	1
the	1
magnitude	1
of	1
the	1
event	1
when	1
you	1
learn	1
that	1
the	1
distant	1
"blaze"	1
had	1
really	1
occurred	1
about	1
the	1
time	1
of	1
the	1
death	1
of	1
Luther!	1
The	1
light	1
of	1
the	1
conflagration	1
had	1
been	1
speeding	1
toward	1
us	1
across	1
space	1
at	1
186,000	1
miles	1
a	1
second,	1
yet	1
it	1
has	1
taken	1
nearly	1
three	1
centuries	1
to	1
reach	1
us.	1
To	1
be	1
visible	1
at	1
all	1
to	1
us	1
at	1
that	1
distance	1
the	1
fiery	1
outbreak	1
must	1
have	1
been	1
stupendous.	1
If	1
a	1
mass	1
of	1
petroleum	1
ten	1
times	1
the	1
size	1
of	1
the	1
