But	1
there	1
is	1
a	1
device	1
whereby	1
the	1
power	1
of	1
these	1
giant	1
instruments,	1
great	1
as	1
it	1
is,	1
can	1
be	1
still	1
further	1
heightened.	1
That	1
device	1
is	1
the	1
simple	1
one	1
of	1
allowing	1
the	1
photographic	1
plate	1
to	1
take	1
the	1
place	1
of	1
the	1
human	1
eye.	1
Nowadays	1
an	1
astronomer	1
seldom	1
spends	1
the	1
night	1
with	1
his	1
eye	1
glued	1
to	1
the	1
great	1
telescope.	1
He	1
puts	1
a	1
photographic	1
plate	1
there.	1
The	1
photographic	1
plate	1
has	1
this	1
advantage	1
over	1
the	1
eye,	1
that	1
it	1
builds	1
up	1
impressions.	1
However	1
long	1
we	1
stare	1
at	1
an	1
