Reflex	1
Actions	1
Among	1
simple	1
multicellular	1
animals,	1
such	1
as	1
sea-anemones,	1
we	1
find	1
the	1
beginnings	1
of	1
reflex	1
actions,	1
and	1
a	1
considerable	1
part	1
of	1
the	1
behaviour	1
of	1
the	1
lower	1
animals	1
is	1
reflex.	1
That	1
is	1
to	1
say,	1
there	1
are	1
laid	1
down	1
in	1
the	1
animal	1
in	1
the	1
course	1
of	1
its	1
development	1
certain	1
pre-arrangements	1
of	1
nerve-cells	1
and	1
muscle-cells	1
which	1
secure	1
that	1
a	1
fit	1
and	1
proper	1
answer	1
is	1
given	1
to	1
a	1
frequently	1
recurrent	1
stimulus.	1
An	1
earthworm	1
half	1
out	1
of	1
its	1
burrow	1
becomes	1
aware	1
of	1
the	1
light	1
tread	1
of	1
a	1
thrush's	1
foot,	1
and	1
jerks	1
itself	1
back	1
into	1
its	1
hole	1
before	1
anyone	1
can	1
say	1
"reflex	1
action."	1
What	1
is	1
it	1
that	1
happens?	1
Certain	1
sensory	1
nerve-cells	1
in	1
the	1
earthworm's	1
skin	1
are	1
stimulated	1
by	1
vibrations	1
in	1
the	1
earth;	1
the	1
message	1
travels	1
down	1
a	1
sensory	1
nerve-fibre	1
from	1
each	1
of	1
the	1
stimulated	1
cells	1
and	1
enters	1
the	1
nerve-cord.	1
The	1
sensory	1
fibres	1
come	1
into	1
vital	1
connection	1
with	1
branches	1
of	1
intermediary,	1
associative,	1
or	1
communicating	1
cells,	1
which	1
are	1
likewise	1
connected	1
with	1
motor	1
nerve-cells.	1
To	1
these	1
the	1
message	1
is	1
thus	1
shunted.	1
From	1
the	1
motor	1
nerve-cells	1
an	1
impulse	1
or	1
command	1
travels	1
by	1
motor	1
nerve-fibres,	1
one	1
from	1
each	1
cell,	1
to	1
the	1
muscles,	1
which	1
contract.	1
If	1
this	1
took	1
as	1
long	1
to	1
happen	1
as	1
it	1
takes	1
to	1
describe,	1
even	1
in	1
outline,	1
it	1
would	1
not	1
be	1
of	1
much	1
use	1
to	1
the	1
earthworm.	1
But	1
the	1
motor	1
answer	1
follows	1
the	1
sensory	1
stimulus	1
almost	1
instantaneously.	1
The	1
great	1
advantage	1
of	1
establishing	1
or	1
enregistering	1
these	1
reflex	1
chains	1
is	1
that	1
the	1
answers	1
are	1
practically	1
ready-made	1
or	1
inborn,	1
not	1
requiring	1
to	1
be	1
learned.	1
It	1
is	1
not	1
necessary	1
that	1
the	1
brain	1
should	1
be	1
stimulated	1
if	1
there	1
is	1
a	1
brain;	1
