§	1
2	1
Factors	1
in	1
Evolution	1
If	1
it	1
be	1
said	1
"So	1
much	1
for	1
the	1
_fact_	1
of	1
evolution,	1
but	1
what	1
of	1
the	1
_factors_?"	1
the	1
answer	1
is	1
not	1
easy.	1
For	1
not	1
only	1
is	1
the	1
problem	1
the	1
greatest	1
of	1
all	1
scientific	1
problems,	1
but	1
the	1
inquiry	1
is	1
still	1
very	1
young.	1
The	1
scientific	1
study	1
of	1
evolution	1
practically	1
dates	1
from	1
the	1
publication	1
of	1
_The	1
Origin	1
of	1
Species_	1
in	1
1859.	1
Heritable	1
novelties	1
or	1
variations	1
often	1
crop	1
up	1
in	1
living	1
creatures,	1
and	1
these	1
form	1
the	1
raw	1
material	1
of	1
evolution.	1
These	1
variations	1
are	1
the	1
outcome	1
of	1
expression	1
of	1
changes	1
in	1
the	1
germ-cells	1
that	1
develop	1
into	1
organisms.	1
But	1
why	1
should	1
there	1
be	1
changes	1
in	1
the	1
constitution	1
of	1
the	1
germ-cells?	1
Perhaps	1
because	1
the	1
living	1
material	1
is	1
very	1
complex	1
and	1
inherently	1
