in	1
and	1
preparatory	1
to	1
this	1
fertilisation	1
may	1
make	1
new	1
permutations	1
and	1
combinations	1
of	1
the	1
living	1
items	1
and	1
hereditary	1
qualities	1
not	1
only	1
possible	1
but	1
necessary.	1
It	1
is	1
something	1
like	1
shuffling	1
a	1
pack	1
of	1
cards,	1
but	1
the	1
cards	1
are	1
living.	1
As	1
to	1
the	1
changes	1
wrought	1
on	1
the	1
body	1
during	1
its	1
lifetime	1
by	1
peculiarities	1
in	1
nurture,	1
habits,	1
and	1
surroundings,	1
these	1
dents	1
or	1
modifications	1
are	1
often	1
very	1
important	1
for	1
the	1
individual,	1
but	1
it	1
does	1
not	1
follow	1
that	1
they	1
are	1
directly	1
important	1
for	1
the	1
race,	1
since	1
it	1
is	1
not	1
certain	1
that	1
they	1
are	1
transmissible.	1
Given	1
a	1
