the	1
answers-back	1
that	1
living	1
creatures	1
make	1
to	1
environing	1
difficulties	1
and	1
limitations.	1
There	1
is	1
struggle	1
for	1
food,	1
accentuated	1
by	1
the	1
fact	1
that	1
small	1
items	1
tend	1
to	1
be	1
swept	1
away	1
by	1
the	1
outgoing	1
tide	1
or	1
to	1
sink	1
down	1
the	1
slope	1
to	1
deep	1
water.	1
Apart	1
from	1
direct	1
competition,	1
e.g.	1
between	1
hungry	1
hermit-crabs,	1
it	1
often	1
involves	1
hard	1
work	1
to	1
get	1
a	1
meal.	1
This	1
is	1
true	1
even	1
of	1
