and	1
Southern	1
India.	1
They	1
are	1
adapted	1
for	1
life	1
on	1
trees,	1
where	1
they	1
hunt	1
insects	1
with	1
great	1
deliberateness	1
and	1
success.	1
The	1
protrusible	1
tongue,	1
ending	1
in	1
a	1
sticky	1
club,	1
can	1
be	1
shot	1
out	1
for	1
about	1
seven	1
inches	1
in	1
the	1
common	1
chameleon.	1
Their	1
hands	1
and	1
feet	1
are	1
split	1
so	1
that	1
they	1
grip	1
the	1
branches	1
firmly,	1
and	1
