Primitive	1
Men	1
Ancient	1
skeletons	1
of	1
men	1
of	1
the	1
modern	1
type	1
have	1
been	1
found	1
in	1
many	1
places,	1
e.g.	1
Combe	1
Capelle	1
in	1
Dordogne,	1
Galley	1
Hill	1
in	1
Kent,	1
Cro-Magnon	1
in	1
Pégord,	1
Mentone	1
on	1
the	1
Riviera;	1
and	1
they	1
are	1
often	1
referred	1
to	1
as	1
"Cave-men"	1
or	1
"men	1
of	1
the	1
Early	1
Stone	1
Age."	1
They	1
had	1
large	1
skulls,	1
high	1
foreheads,	1
well-marked	1
chins,	1
and	1
other	1
features	1
such	1
as	1
modern	1
man	1
possesses.	1
They	1
were	1
true	1
men	1
at	1
last--that	1
is	1
to	1
say,	1
like	1
ourselves!	1
The	1
spirited	1
pictures	1
they	1
made	1
on	1
the	1
walls	1
of	1
caves	1
in	1
France	1
and	1
Spain	1
show	1
artistic	1
sense	1
and	1
skill.	1
Well-finished	1
