Factors	1
in	1
Human	1
Progress	1
Many,	1
we	1
believe,	1
were	1
the	1
gains	1
that	1
rewarded	1
the	1
arboreal	1
apprenticeship	1
of	1
man's	1
ancestors.	1
Many,	1
likewise,	1
were	1
the	1
results	1
of	1
leaving	1
the	1
trees	1
and	1
coming	1
down	1
to	1
the	1
solid	1
earth--a	1
transition	1
which	1
marked	1
the	1
emergence	1
of	1
more	1
than	1
tentative	1
men.	1
What	1
great	1
steps	1
followed?	1
Some	1
of	1
the	1
greatest	1
were--the	1
working	1
out	1
of	1
a	1
spoken	1
language	1
and	1
of	1
external	1
methods	1
of	1
registration;	1
the	1
invention	1
of	1
tools;	1
the	1
discovery	1
of	1
the	1
use	1
of	1
fire;	1
the	1
utilisation	1
of	1
iron	1
and	1
other	1
metals;	1
the	1
taming	1
of	1
wild	1
animals	1
such	1
as	1
dog	1
and	1
sheep,	1
horses	1
and	1
cattle;	1
the	1
cultivation	1
of	1
wild	1
plants	1
such	1
as	1
wheat	1
and	1
rice;	1
and	1
the	1
irrigation	1
of	1
fields.	1
All	1
through	1
the	1
ages	1
necessity	1
has	1
been	1
the	1
mother	1
of	1
invention	1
and	1
curiosity	1
its	1
father;	1
but	1
perhaps	1
we	1
miss	1
the	1
heart	1
of	1
the	1
matter	1
if	1
we	1
forget	1
the	1
importance	1
of	1
some	1
leisure	1
time--wherein	1
to	1
observe	1
and	1
think.	1
If	1
our	1
earth	1
had	1
been	1
so	1
clouded	1
that	1
the	1
stars	1
were	1
hidden	1
from	1
men's	1
eyes	1
the	1
whole	1
history	1
of	1
our	1
race	1
would	1
have	1
been	1
different.	1
For	1
it	1
was	1
through	1
his	1
leisure-time	1
observations	1
of	1
the	1
stars	1
that	1
early	1
man	1
discovered	1
the	1
regularity	1
of	1
the	1
year	1
and	1
got	1
his	1
fundamental	1
impressions	1
of	1
the	1
order	1
of	1
Nature--on	1
which	1
all	1
his	1
science	1
is	1
founded.	1
If	1
we	1
are	1
to	1
think	1
clearly	1
of	1
the	1
factors	1
of	1
human	1
progress	1
we	1
must	1
recall	1
the	1
three	1
great	1
biological	1
ideas--the	1
living	1
organism,	1
its	1
environment,	1
and	1
its	1
functioning.	1
For	1
man	1
these	1
mean	1
(1)	1
the	1
living	1
creature,	1
the	1
outcome	1
of	1
parents	1
and	1
ancestors,	1
a	1
fresh	1
expression	1
of	1
a	1
bodily	1
and	1
mental	1
inheritance;	1
(2)	1
the	1
surroundings,	1
including	1
climate	1
and	1
soil,	1
the	1
plants	1
and	1
animals	1
these	1
allow;	1
and	1
(3)	1
the	1
activities	1
of	1
all	1
sorts,	1
occupations	1
and	1
habits,	1
all	1
