The	1
Story	1
of	1
the	1
Salmon	1
In	1
late	1
autumn	1
or	1
in	1
winter	1
the	1
salmon	1
spawn	1
in	1
the	1
rivers.	1
The	1
female	1
makes	1
a	1
shallow	1
trough	1
in	1
the	1
gravel	1
by	1
moving	1
her	1
tail	1
from	1
side	1
to	1
side,	1
and	1
therein	1
lays	1
many	1
eggs.	1
The	1
male,	1
who	1
is	1
in	1
attendance,	1
fertilises	1
these	1
with	1
the	1
milt,	1
and	1
then	1
the	1
female	1
covers	1
them	1
deeply	1
with	1
gravel.	1
The	1
process	1
is	1
repeated	1
over	1
and	1
over	1
again	1
for	1
a	1
week	1
or	1
more	1
till	1
all	1
the	1
eggs	1
are	1
shed.	1
For	1
three	1
to	1
four	1
months	1
the	1
eggs	1
develop,	1
and	1
eventually	1
there	1
emerge	1
the	1
larvær	1
_alevins_,	1
which	1
lurk	1
among	1
the	1
