new	1
variations	1
and	1
their	1
sifting,	1
by	1
experimenting	1
and	1
enregistering	1
the	1
results,	1
the	1
mind	1
has	1
gradually	1
evolved	1
and	1
will	1
continue	1
to	1
evolve.	1
VIII	1
FOUNDATIONS	1
OF	1
THE	1
UNIVERSE	1
THE	1
WORLD	1
OF	1
ATOMS	1
Most	1
people	1
have	1
heard	1
of	1
the	1
oriental	1
race	1
which	1
puzzled	1
over	1
the	1
foundations	1
of	1
the	1
universe,	1
and	1
decided	1
that	1
it	1
must	1
be	1
supported	1
on	1
the	1
back	1
of	1
a	1
giant	1
elephant.	1
But	1
the	1
elephant?	1
They	1
put	1
it	1
on	1
the	1
back	1
of	1
a	1
monstrous	1
tortoise,	1
and	1
there	1
they	1
let	1
the	1
matter	1
end.	1
If	1
every	1
animal	1
in	1
nature	1
had	1
been	1
called	1
upon,	1
they	1
would	1
have	1
been	1
no	1
nearer	1
a	1
foundation.	1
Most	1
ancient	1
peoples,	1
indeed,	1
made	1
no	1
effort	1
to	1
find	1
a	1
foundation.	1
The	1
universe	1
was	1
a	1
very	1
compact	1
little	1
structure,	1
mainly	1
composed	1
of	1
the	1
earth	1
and	1
the	1
great	1
canopy	1
over	1
the	1
earth	1
which	1
they	1
called	1
the	1
sky.	1
They	1
left	1
it,	1
as	1
a	1
whole,	1
floating	1
in	1
nothing.	1
And	1
in	1
this	1
the	1
ancients	1
were	1
wiser	1
than	1
they	1
knew.	1
Things	1
do	1
not	1
fall	1
down	1
unless	1
they	1
are	1
pulled	1
down	1
by	1
that	1
mysterious	1
force	1
which	1
we	1
call	1
gravitation.	1
The	1
earth,	1
it	1
is	1
true,	1
is	1
pulled	1
by	1
the	1
sun,	1
and	1
would	1
fall	1
into	1
it;	1
but	1
the	1
earth	1
escapes	1
this	1
fiery	1
fate	1
by	1
circulating	1
at	1
great	1
speed	1
round	1
the	1
sun.	1
The	1
stars	1
pull	1
each	1
other;	1
but	1
it	1
has	1
already	1
been	1
explained	1
that	1
they	1
meet	1
this	1
by	1
travelling	1
rapidly	1
in	1
gigantic	1
orbits.	1
Yet	1
we	1
do,	1
in	1
a	1
new	1
sense	1
of	1
the	1
word,	1
need	1
foundations	1
of	1
the	1
universe.	1
Our	1
mind	1
craves	1
for	1
some	1
explanation	1
of	1
the	1
matter	1
out	1
of	1
which	1
the	1
universe	1
is	1
made.	1
For	1
this	1
explanation	1
we	1
turn	1
to	1
modern	1
Physics	1
and	1
Chemistry.	1
Both	1
these	1
sciences	1
study,	1
under	1
different	1
aspects,	1
matter	1
and	1
energy;	1
and	1
between	1
them	1
they	1
have	1
put	1
together	1
a	1
conception	1
of	1
the	1
fundamental	1
nature	1
of	1
things	1
which	1
marks	1
an	1
epoch	1
in	1
the	1
history	1
of	1
human	1
thought.	1
§	1
1	1
The	1
Bricks	1
of	1
the	1
Cosmos	1
More	1
than	1
two	1
thousand	1
years	1
ago	1
the	1
first	1
men	1
of	1
science,	1
the	1
Greeks	1
of	1
the	1
cities	1
of	1
Asia	1
Minor,	1
speculated	1
on	1
the	1
nature	1
of	1
matter.	1
You	1
can	1
grind	1
a	1
piece	1
of	1
stone	1
into	1
dust.	1
You	1
can	1
divide	1
a	1
spoonful	1
of	1
water	1
into	1
as	1
many	1
drops	1
as	1
you	1
like.	1
Apparently	1
you	1
can	1
go	1
on	1
dividing	1
as	1
long	1
as	1
you	1
have	1
got	1
apparatus	1
fine	1
enough	1
for	1
the	1
work.	1
But	1
there	1
must	1
be	1
a	1
limit,	1
these	1
Greeks	1
said,	1
and	1
so	1
they	1
supposed	1
that	1
all	1
matter	1
was	1
ultimately	1
composed	1
of	1
minute	1
particles	1
which	1
were	1
