but	1
he	1
did	1
not	1
fully	1
appreciate	1
the	1
nature	1
of	1
his	1
experiments.]	1
[Illustration:	1
_Photo:	1
Photo	1
Press_	1
PROFESSOR	1
SIR	1
W.	1
H.	1
BRAGG	1
One	1
of	1
the	1
most	1
distinguished	1
physicists	1
of	1
the	1
present	1
day.]	1
But	1
if	1
we	1
had	1
some	1
magical	1
glass	1
by	1
means	1
of	1
which	1
we	1
could	1
see	1
into	1
the	1
structure	1
of	1
material	1
things,	1
we	1
should	1
not	1
see	1
the	1
atoms	1
put	1
evenly	1
together	1
as	1
bricks	1
are	1
in	1
a	1
wall.	1
As	1
a	1
rule,	1
two	1
or	1
more	1
atoms	1
first	1
come	1
together	1
to	1
form	1
a	1
