§	1
12	1
What	1
the	1
Blue	1
"Sky"	1
means	1
We	1
saw	1
in	1
a	1
previous	1
chapter	1
how	1
the	1
spectroscope	1
splits	1
up	1
light-waves	1
into	1
their	1
colours.	1
But	1
nature	1
is	1
constantly	1
splitting	1
the	1
light	1
into	1
its	1
different-lengthed	1
waves,	1
its	1
colours.	1
The	1
rainbow,	1
where	1
dense	1
moisture	1
in	1
the	1
air	1
acts	1
as	1
a	1
spectroscope,	1
is	1
the	1
most	1
familiar	1
example.	1
A	1
piece	1
of	1
mother-of-pearl,	1
or	1
even	1
a	1
film	1
of	1
oil	1
on	1
the	1
street	1
or	1
