water,	1
has	1
the	1
same	1
effect,	1
owing	1
to	1
the	1
fine	1
inequalities	1
in	1
its	1
surface.	1
The	1
atmosphere	1
all	1
day	1
long	1
is	1
sorting	1
out	1
the	1
waves.	1
The	1
blue	1
"sky"	1
overhead	1
means	1
that	1
the	1
fine	1
particles	1
in	1
the	1
upper	1
atmosphere	1
catch	1
the	1
shorter	1
waves,	1
the	1
blue	1
waves,	1
and	1
scatter	1
them.	1
We	1
can	1
make	1
a	1
tubeful	1
of	1
blue	1
sky	1
in	1
the	1
laboratory	1
at	1
any	1
time.	1
The	1
beautiful	1
pink-flush	1
on	1
the	1
Alps	1
at	1
sunrise,	1
the	1
red	1
glory	1
that	1
lingers	1
in	1
the	1
west	1
at	1
sunset,	1
mean	1
that,	1
as	1
the	1
sun's	1
rays	1
must	1
struggle	1
through	1
denser	1
masses	1
of	1
air	1
when	1
it	1
is	1
low	1
on	1
the	1
horizon,	1
the	1
long	1
red	1
waves	1
are	1
sifted	1
out	1
from	1
the	1
other	1
shafts.	1
Then	1
there	1
is	1
the	1
varied	1
face	1
of	1
nature	1
which,	1
by	1
absorbing	1
some	1
waves	1
and	1
reflecting	1
others,	1
weaves	1
its	1
own	1
beautiful	1
