The	1
Earth	1
Slowing	1
down	1
The	1
answer	1
is	1
simple,	1
but	1
startling.	1
_The	1
source	1
of	1
tidal	1
energy	1
is	1
the	1
rotation	1
of	1
the	1
earth._	1
The	1
massive	1
bulk	1
of	1
the	1
earth,	1
turning	1
every	1
twenty-four	1
hours	1
on	1
its	1
axis,	1
is	1
like	1
a	1
gigantic	1
flywheel.	1
In	1
virtue	1
of	1
its	1
rotation	1
it	1
possesses	1
an	1
enormous	1
store	1
of	1
energy.	1
But	1
even	1
the	1
heaviest	1
and	1
swiftest	1
flywheel,	1
if	1
it	1
is	1
doing	1
work,	1
or	1
even	1
if	1
it	1
is	1
only	1
working	1
against	1
the	1
friction	1
of	1
its	1
bearings,	1
cannot	1
dispense	1
energy	1
for	1
ever.	1
It	1
must,	1
gradually,	1
slow	1
down.	1
There	1
is	1
no	1
escape	1
from	1
this	1
reasoning.	1
It	1
is	1
the	1
rotation	1
of	1
the	1
earth	1
which	1
supplies	1
the	1
energy	1
of	1
the	1
tides,	1
and,	1
as	1
a	1
consequence,	1
the	1
tides	1
must	1
be	1
slowing	1
down	1
the	1
earth.	1
The	1
tides	1
act	1
as	1
a	1
kind	1
of	1
brake	1
on	1
the	1
earth's	1
rotation.	1
These	1
masses	1
of	1
water,	1
_held	1
back	1
by	1
the	1
moon_,	1
exert	1
a	1
kind	1
of	1
dragging	1
effect	1
on	1
the	1
rotating	1
earth.	1
Doubtless	1
